Cape Town - Bus drivers employed by MyCiTi bus vehicle operating companies have embarked on a wildcat strike on Monday morning, Member of the Mayoral Committee: Transport and Urban Development Brett Herron said. "There are reports of intimidation of those drivers who are working. Striking bus drivers are apparently blocking red roads." He also apologised to affected commuters. There are currently no buses operating on routes A01, T01, T03, T04, 101, 102, 103,104, 105, 106, 107, 108, 109, 213, 214, 215, 216, 217, 230, 251, 260, 261, 262 and a limited services on routes T02, D01, D02, D03, D04, @MyCiTiBus tweeted. The strike is expected to add more strain on commuters already suffering under an unreliable rail transport system.      * This is a developing story and will be updated as more information becomes available. ** Receive IOL's top stories via Whatsapp by sending your name to 0745573535. IOL